        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 1:16PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 115 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rainbow City, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Gadsden, Rainbow City, Attalla, Glencoe, Ohatchee, Steele, Gadsden
Mall, Neely Henry Lake, Southside, Alabama International Dragway,
Gadsden Steam Plant, Big Wills Creek, Gadsden Municipal Airport,
Northside, Gadsden Water Works, and Ramsey.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
